<subSubSection id="C357656EFFF1FFD34D2F045EFC34FAB6" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF236E5FFF1FFD34D2F045EFC34FAB6" blockId="7.[811,1457,818,1345]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
DIAGNOSIS (BASED ON NEW MATERIAL). — Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D66FFF1FFD34B39045EFA27FCBD" authorityName="Wall" authorityYear="1908" box="[1339,1456,818,842]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Dendrelaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="biloreatus">
<emphasis id="B939EAF7FFF1FFD34B39045EFA27FCBD" box="[1339,1456,818,842]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">D. biloreatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(N = 4) are diagnosed by the combination of: 1) brownish dorsum with a black stripe on each side of head extending up to the neck; 2) upper and lower lips and chin yellowish; 3) Ve 
<quantity id="4CB59B00FFF1FFD34B1B04EFFACDFC6E" box="[1305,1370,897,922]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1562" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="in" value="203.0">203 in</quantity>
females, 
<quantity id="4CB59B00FFF1FFD34D2F04F1FC0CFC43" box="[813,923,924,948]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9276" metricValueMax="5.0292" metricValueMin="4.826" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="in" value="194.0" valueMax="198.0" valueMin="190.0">190-198 in</quantity>
male; 4) paired Sc 
<quantity id="4CB59B00FFF1FFD34A5A04F1FB50FC43" box="[1112,1223,924,948]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6576" metricValueMax="3.8354" metricValueMin="3.4798" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="in" value="144.0" valueMax="151.0" valueMin="137.0">137-151 in</quantity>
males, 
<quantity id="4CB59B00FFF1FFD34B1304F1FAC6FC43" box="[1297,1361,924,948]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5907999999999998" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="in" value="102.0">102 in</quantity>
damaged tail female; 5) divided As; 6) Ls 1-2; 7) PrO 1; 8) PoO 2; 9) Te 1+2, 2+2, 2+3; 10) 4th–5th SLE; 11) IF 10; 12) SL 8; 13) DSR 13:13:11; and 14) average RTaL 0.32 (0.26-0.36) in males, and 
<quantity id="4CB59B00FFF1FFD34B420486FA10FBF4" box="[1344,1415,1003,1027]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.112" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="in" value="0.28">0.28 in</quantity>
the damaged tail female. The new materials from this study updated the known morphological characters as follows: upper limit of Ve 190-203 vs 192 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B14FFF1FFD34DD20356FBA4FBA4" author="Wall" box="[976,1075,1083,1107]" firstAuthor="Wall" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" pagination="272 - 274" refId="ref14003" refString="WALL F. 1908. - Two new snakes from Assam. Journal of Bombay Natural History Society 18: 272 - 274." type="journal article" year="1908">Wall 1908</bibRefCitation>
) and 187-199 as 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D66FFF1FFD34ADB0356FA3DFBA4" authority="(Smith 1943)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1943" box="[1241,1450,1083,1107]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Dendrelaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gorei">
<emphasis id="B939EAF7FFF1FFD34ADB0356FAB4FBA5" box="[1241,1315,1083,1106]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">D. gorei</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B14FFF1FFD34B2D0356FA37FBA4" author="Smith" box="[1327,1440,1083,1107]" firstAuthor="Smith" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" refId="ref13321" refString="SMITH M. A. 1943. - The fauna of British India, Ceylon and Burma. Reptilia and Amphibia. Volume 3. Serpentes. Taylor &amp; Francis, UK." type="book" year="1943">Smith 1943</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; lower limit of Sc 137-151 vs 147 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B14FFF1FFD34A640338FB50FB9A" author="Wall" box="[1126,1223,1109,1133]" firstAuthor="Wall" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" pagination="272 - 274" refId="ref14003" refString="WALL F. 1908. - Two new snakes from Assam. Journal of Bombay Natural History Society 18: 272 - 274." type="journal article" year="1908">Wall 1908</bibRefCitation>
) and 139-154 as 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D66FFF1FFD34B6A033BFC25FB7F" authority="(Smith 1943)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1943" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Dendrelaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gorei">
<emphasis id="B939EAF7FFF1FFD34B6A033BFA39FB9A" box="[1384,1454,1110,1133]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">D. gorei</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B14FFF1FFD34D37031DFC3EFB7F" author="Smith" box="[821,937,1136,1160]" firstAuthor="Smith" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" refId="ref13321" refString="SMITH M. A. 1943. - The fauna of British India, Ceylon and Burma. Reptilia and Amphibia. Volume 3. Serpentes. Taylor &amp; Francis, UK." type="book" year="1943">Smith 1943</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; Te 1+2, 2+2, 2+3 vs 1+1 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B14FFF1FFD34AB8031DFAB7FB7F" author="Wall" box="[1210,1312,1136,1160]" firstAuthor="Wall" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" pagination="272 - 274" refId="ref14003" refString="WALL F. 1908. - Two new snakes from Assam. Journal of Bombay Natural History Society 18: 272 - 274." type="journal article" year="1908">Wall 1908</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B14FFF1FFD34B2F031DFA36FB7F" author="Smith" box="[1325,1441,1136,1160]" firstAuthor="Smith" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" refId="ref13321" refString="SMITH M. A. 1943. - The fauna of British India, Ceylon and Burma. Reptilia and Amphibia. Volume 3. Serpentes. Taylor &amp; Francis, UK." type="book" year="1943">Smith 1943</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, we provide brief comparative morphological data between 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D66FFF1FFD34D6C03C8FC68FB4B" authorityName="MZMU" baseAuthorityName="Wall" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[878,1023,1188,1212]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Dendrelaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cyanochloris">
<emphasis id="B939EAF7FFF1FFD34D6C03C8FC68FB4B" box="[878,1023,1188,1212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">D. cyanochloris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D66FFF1FFD34A0F03C8FB12FB4B" authorityName="Wall" authorityYear="1909" box="[1037,1157,1188,1212]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Dendrelaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="proarchos">
<emphasis id="B939EAF7FFF1FFD34A0F03C8FB12FB4B" box="[1037,1157,1188,1212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">D. proarchos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D66FFF1FFD34AC303C8FAABFB4B" authorityName="Wall" authorityYear="1908" box="[1217,1340,1188,1212]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Dendrelaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="biloreatus">
<emphasis id="B939EAF7FFF1FFD34AC303C8FAABFB4B" box="[1217,1340,1188,1212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">D. biloreatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other zoological collections, along with the new 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D66FFF1FFD34ACE03D2FAD0FB20" authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1890" box="[1228,1351,1215,1239]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Dendrelaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B939EAF7FFF1FFD34ACE03D2FAD0FB20" box="[1228,1351,1215,1239]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Dendrelaphis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens collected from 
<collectingRegion id="4989F807FFF1FFD34DC103B4FBC2FB05" box="[963,1109,1241,1266]" country="India" name="Mizoram" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Mizoram State</collectingRegion>
(
<tableCitation id="C6CF035EFFF1FFD34A6603B4FB38FB05" box="[1124,1199,1241,1266]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="9.[126,137,655,677]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="TABLE 1. — Morphometric (in mm) and scalation data of Dendrelaphis Boulenger, 1890 species examined for this study. Paired values are given as left/right order.Symbol:* indicates damaged or incomplete characters, and hyphens indicate unavailable data)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF32666DFFFFFFDD4E7C05E2FE5EFD4C" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" tableUuid="DF32666DFFFFFFDD4E7C05E2FE5EFD4C">Table 1</tableCitation>
). See 
<figureCitation id="13762A60FFF1FFD34AED03B4FAF3FB05" box="[1263,1380,1241,1266]" captionStart="APPENDIX" captionStartId="18.[132,144,305,323]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="APPENDIX 1. — Distributional data of Dendrelaphis species documented in Mizoram State with date, locality, coordinates, and elevation (in meters a.s.l.). Bold voucher numbers denote the specimens used for the molecular analysis. Symbol: *, specimen not vouchered." pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Appendix 1</figureCitation>
for the detailed collection records, and 
<figureCitation id="13762A60FFF1FFD34A640399FB4EFAFB" box="[1126,1241,1268,1292]" captionStart="APPENDIX" captionStartId="19.[133,145,221,239]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="APPENDIX 2. — Morphometric (in mm) and scalation data of Dendrelaphis proarchos Wall, 1909 (Dp), Dendrelaphis cyanochloris (Wall, 1921) (Dc) and Dendrela-" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Appendix 2</figureCitation>
for the morphometry and scalation data of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D66FFF1FFD34DF90263FB29FAD1" box="[1019,1214,1294,1318]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
<emphasis id="B939EAF7FFF1FFD34DF90263FBE1FAD1" box="[1019,1142,1294,1318]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Dendrelaphis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
collected from 
<collectingRegion id="4989F807FFF1FFD34B570263FCC8FAB6" country="India" name="Mizoram" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Mizoram State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F35A7675FFF1FFD34D6B0244FC37FAB6" box="[873,928,1321,1345]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C357656EFFF1FFD34D2F0237FC64FA02" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BF236E5FFF1FFD34D2F0237FC64FA02" blockId="7.[813,1455,1368,1525]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
GEOGRAPHICAL DISTRIBUTION. —This species inhabits the Assam Valley with the adjoining Himalayan foothills, and northern parts of 
<collectingCountry id="F35A7675FFF1FFD34D4B02E3FC3DFA51" box="[841,938,1422,1446]" name="Myanmar" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
near the border with Assam (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B14FFF1FFD34AD802E0FCF9FA37" author="Vogel &amp; van Rooijen" firstAuthor="Vogel" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" pagination="17 - 24" refId="ref13871" refString="VOGEL G. &amp; VAN ROOIJEN J. 2011 b. - Description of a new species of the genus Dendrelaphis Boulenger, 1890 from Myanmar (Squamata: Serpentes: Colubridae). Bonn Zoological Bulletin 60: 17 - 24." type="journal article" year="2011" yearSuffix="b">Vogel &amp; van Rooijen 2011b</bibRefCitation>
). In this work, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D66FFF1FFD34A0302C4FBEDFA37" authorityName="Wall" authorityYear="1908" box="[1025,1146,1448,1472]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Dendrelaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="biloreatus">
<emphasis id="B939EAF7FFF1FFD34A0302C4FBEDFA37" box="[1025,1146,1448,1472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">D. biloreatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is documented from four localities in Mizoram state at the elevation range of 
<quantity id="4CB59B00FFF1FFD34AF802AFFAEBFA2D" box="[1274,1404,1474,1498]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.315" metricValueMax="14.2" metricValueMin="4.43" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="m" value="931.5" valueMax="1420.0" valueMin="443.0">443-1,420 m</quantity>
a.s.l. (
<figureCitation id="13762A60FFF1FFD34D3602B0FCF9FA03" box="[820,878,1500,1525]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="12.[131,142,1606,1624]" captionTargetBox="[132,1456,184,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-290@12.[133,1420,252,1560]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIG. 5. — Elevation map showing the specimens location of Dendrelaphis proarchos Wall, 1909 (green shapes), Dendrelaphis biloreatus Wall, 1908 (yellow shapes), Dendrelaphis cyanochloris (Wall, 1921) (red shapes), Dendrelaphis cf. vogeli LSUHC 6768 (purple circle with dot), and Dendelaphis cf. ngansonensis CAS221428 (blue circle with dot) examined in this study. Confirmed populations of Dendrelaphis proarchos (green circles) and Dendrelaphis biloreatus (yellow triangles) are based on Vogel &amp; van Rooijen (2011a, b)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6421951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6421951/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13762A60FFF1FFD34D7B02B0FC7EFA02" box="[889,1001,1501,1525]" captionStart="APPENDIX" captionStartId="18.[132,144,305,323]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="APPENDIX 1. — Distributional data of Dendrelaphis species documented in Mizoram State with date, locality, coordinates, and elevation (in meters a.s.l.). Bold voucher numbers denote the specimens used for the molecular analysis. Symbol: *, specimen not vouchered." pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Appendix 1</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
